body:
I agree with @mik-laj, Integration.rst was really  "a bag of everything" (see it [here](https://airflow.readthedocs.io/en/latest/integration.html)).

With those changes where we restructure it and separate out types of integration, it is much easier to navigate with the changes above. And we are not removing any information - quite contrary we are adding a lot of "overview" information by having all the tables and splitting integration.rst in a more meaningful way.

@feluelle -> are you afraid that people are used to the old structure of documentation or just linked to the old documentation with URL links ? 

If it's the first, I think it's really well known in the community that we are working on improving documentation so they won't be surprised.

@mik-laj - maybe we can involve the community a bit more and ask them what they think (after the merge - it will be easier via "readthedocs") ? 

I think AIP is a bit overkill for this. However we could just explain community a bit more context - why we are doing it and let and let them see it before we "release it", that would be really nice and  give the community a chance to comment and influence it.
